WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:06.717 --> 00:00:09.805
 It is easy to build new buildings and increase the level of existing ones. 

00:00:09.355 --> 00:00:13.406
 To build new buildings, click on your Castle, then on "Build" next to the type of building you wish to add. 

00:00:15.463 --> 00:00:20.337
 To increase the level of an already built building, click on it and then on "Improve". 

00:00:21.672 --> 00:00:25.682
 To improve your Bastion, it's a little more devious. Click on your Bastion, then on "Enter". 

00:00:25.932 --> 00:00:29.980
 Here, you can improve your Bastion like any other building. 

00:00:30.874 --> 00:00:35.739
 If you drag the mouse over the "Build" button you will see the number of resources needed to build or improve the building. The numbers will appear in red if you do not meet all the conditions. 

00:00:36.960 --> 00:00:40.263
 Once your Mystic Tower is built, you will be able to search for skills. 

00:00:40.320 --> 00:00:43.964
 Just click on Mystique Tower and then on "Train" next to the desired skill. 

00:00:44.077 --> 00:00:47.677
 You will find all the information about the skill in its description. 

00:00:47.935 --> 00:00:50.935
 ... but also for your Heroes. 

00:00:52.934 --> 00:00:56.984
 Heroes are divided into 5 different levels - White, Blue, Yellow, Green and Purple 

00:00:58.561 --> 00:01:04.465
 After building and upgrading your Tavern, you will have the opportunity to recruit higher level Heroes. 

00:01:05.672 --> 00:01:15.930
 Once you have recruited a Hero, you can equip him with items, allocate troops and, of course, send him to fight against the World Map Monsters or in the Arena. 

00:01:20.248 --> 00:01:27.800
 When your Heroes Tour is built, you can name a Castellan, who, depending on his skills, will increase the number of resources and gold produced. 

00:01:29.710 --> 00:01:34.263
 Your Castellan will also be your first line of defense against enemy attacks. 

00:01:38.956 --> 00:01:43.829
 The embassy will be required to join a Guild, or simply create one. 

00:01:46.045 --> 00:01:52.796
 This is one of the most important buildings if you want to know the community of Castle of Heroes. 

00:01:55.748 --> 00:02:00.980
 Guilds are not just about protecting you, but are essential to the game and the experience you'll have. 

00:02:04.827 --> 00:02:09.317
 In addition to allocating units to your Heroes, you can also improve their stats from the Heroes interface. 

00:02:10.037 --> 00:02:13.955
 You can increase the level of your Heroes by completing quests or fighting enemies. 

00:02:15.157 --> 00:02:21.678
 Once your Hero increases level, you will be able to add points to one of your stats: Attack, Defense, Speed ​​and Intelligence. 

00:02:22.247 --> 00:02:26.311
 You can also equip items to your Heroes to add extra points to their stats. 

00:02:26.415 --> 00:02:30.115
 You can take possession of items either by buying them in your Armory, or by looting the various buildings of the World or other Guardians of Treasures. 

00:02:30.215 --> 00:02:34.585
 On this screen, you can also select the spells you have learned and assign them to your Heroes. 

00:02:38.321 --> 00:02:43.172
 On the Quests screen, you can see all the main Quests, which will help you build buildings, form units, and search for Skills. 

00:02:45.503 --> 00:02:52.069
 or the Daily Quests that will help you get more resources, experience and action points 

00:02:53.091 --> 00:02:54.786
 or the Hero Quests that will allow you to level up quickly at the beginning of your adventure. 

00:02:54.813 --> 00:02:58.813
 Once a Quest is accepted, you will need to complete it in order to receive your reward. 

00:03:03.402 --> 00:03:07.417
 Once out of the Castle, you will be on the World Map. 

00:03:08.497 --> 00:03:15.279
 From there, you can send your Hero to fight monsters or guardians of treasures, 

00:03:17.456 --> 00:03:24.439
 capture enemy Castles or NPCs or mines 

00:03:28.197 --> 00:03:34.941
 or attack the buildings of the World to increase your Fame / experience and benefit from temporary improvements (increase your speed ...) 

00:03:38.603 --> 00:03:43.619
 Once you have reached a fame of 2200 and your army has about 250,000 units, you can seize a Secondary Castle. 

00:03:44.428 --> 00:03:50.387
 Click on an NPC Castle, then "Occupy" and select the Hero that will attack it. 

00:03:54.400 --> 00:04:00.290
 Once your Hero arrives at this Castle and defeats the opposing defenses, the Castle will belong to you. 

00:04:21.920 --> 00:04:29.376
 You will need a good level of Renown to attack some Buildings of the World. 

00:04:32.104 --> 00:04:40.984
 The Buildings of the World will give you experience, fame, resources and other accessories. 

00:04:59.069 --> 00:05:02.973
 You have access to chat all the time except in combat. 

00:05:03.089 --> 00:05:07.135
 The "General" chat connects all players online (ie the chat will be available to all players currently in play) 

00:05:07.323 --> 00:05:11.364
 The Guild Chat can only be seen and read by members of your Guild and can only be used once you join a Guild. 

00:05:11.849 --> 00:05:15.856
 The "Private" chat if you want to talk with a particular player. 

00:05:20.887 --> 00:05:24.915
 If you are not afraid of challenges, you can send your hero to fight in the arena. 

00:05:25.751 --> 00:05:29.831
 Just select the arena corresponding to your hero's level and click on "Enter" 

00:05:32.134 --> 00:05:38.011
 When two players are in the queue waiting for a fight, the battle will begin. 

00:05:48.443 --> 00:05:54.019
 The players will receive a number of fame points that will allow them to have more room for their troops and give them access to additional items. 

